<br>
How much mana does each point of int give?<br>
I've seen people mention the change to formula when you have above 200 and I *think* before 200 it was something like :<br>
<br>
1 point of int = level/5 points of mana.<br>
<br>
Is this correct? and what about above 200 int?<br>
<br>
[and yes I have tried the mystical search button] <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=sardonus>Sardonus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 124<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/28/03 8:42 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: int to mana ratio....again</span><hr size=1> The equations I believe to be true are as follows:<br>
<br>
Below 200 int=level/5 mana for each point of int.<br>
<br>
Above 200 int=level/10 mana for each point of int. This equates to 6 int per point at 60 which is why you hear alot of people just straight out say that each point above 200 is worth 6 mana.<br>
<br>
Above 255 int=5 mana per point of int. I came to this conclusion by playing with int on magelo so, I am assuming magelo is correct. If there is a formula for this I have not heard it and magelo seemed pretty straight forward about this. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=yyidth>yyidth</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br>  Posts: 294<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/28/03 9:10 am)</font><br>     <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: int to mana ratio....again</span><hr size=1> Here is a <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/forum_flat.html?mess_num=69534">thread</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> in the Magelo forums that gives the formulas used there. I will warn you the formulas are not as simple as people tend to think they should be.<br>
<br>
Ohh, here is the relevant info for those not interested in clicking on links.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>At or below 200 WI:<br>
<br>
Mana = ( [ 850 * level ] + [ 85 * WI * level ] ) / 425<br>
<br>
This one can be simplified by dividing out a factor of 85, which then yields the commonly known equation of Mana=(10+WI)*Level/5<br>
<br>
At or above 200 WI:<br>
<br>
Mana = ( [ 11,250 * level ] + [ 33 * WI * level ] ) / 425<br>
<br>
This one can't be simplified as the one above (and for similarity reasons, that's why I wrote the one above as I did). Note that the contribution from level above 200 WI is far more important than when you are below 200 WI. At a value of 200 WI, the equations are the same.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--> <p>-- <br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=40498">Yyidth of the Rathe (lvl 63 wizard)</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=gebbly>Gebbly</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br>  Posts: 294<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/28/03 9:30 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> over 200</span><hr size=1> That formula is a bit more complex than I had imagined it would be. Does anyone know *why* the formula is so complex (just curious)? What factors its taking into account?<br>
<br>
Also another small thought. If you have over 200 int is the total mana worked out using purely formula 2 or do they work out mana from your first 200 points of int using formula 1 and any int over 200 with formula 2? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=yyidth>yyidth</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br>  Posts: 296<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/28/03 9:49 am)</font><br>     <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: int to mana ratio....again</span><hr size=1> Gebbly, these formulas have been derived by the magelo gods (that is to say they have not been released by SOE).<br>
<br>
Be careful how you read the above. It has been determined that how much mana a toon has is calculated differently depending on how much int/wis the toon has. Only one formula is used for a toon. The first is used if you have 200 or less int/wis and the second is used if you have 200 or more int/wis. For a toon with 200 int/wis the formulas give the same value of mana.<br>
<br>
It is perhaps worth mentioning that these formulas are post PoP. The way it worked changed at that point. Prior to PoP the first formula was gospel and the second did not exist. <p>-- <br>
